summary:
Why the weird name? It comes from the C stdlib function cbrtl.
But why does the C standard library have these weird names?
Well there is a little bit of trivia to it, in older versions of ANSI C, only the first 6 characters of an identifier were considered in the compiler. So most standard library functions in C have odd names like strstr, strtod, alloca and so on&hellip;
Oh, and also because every other GitHub organization name was taken&hellip;
